FBIS4-55322 "dreeu093_y_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Federal Government Addresses Weapons Smuggling Issue Government Addresses Weapons Smuggling Issue AU1205163694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 12 May 94 AU1205163694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpt] The Federal Government has submitted answers to questions posed by deputies at the Federal Assembly. The government suggests that the law on military schools and military scientific institutions be adopted in an urgent procedure. Let us listen to a report by Mirjana Protic: [Begin Protic recording] The Federal Ministry of Defense asserts that there has so far been no incidence of a Yugoslav Army warehouse being broken into. This is the gist of the reply to a question by a deputy. The weapons used by individuals and illegal military [words indistinct] of members of the NCA [expansion unknown] so far mostly originate from battlefields in the former Bosnia-Herzegovina. They are also brought through various smuggling channels from Turkey via Albania. Certain humanitarian organizations such as Merhamet [word indistinct] channels for smuggling arms to the territory of Raska Region. Several smuggling channels that involved former members of the Yugoslav People's Army of Muslim nationality who had gone over to the Army of the former Bosnia-Herzegovina, have also been discovered. [passage omitted] [end recording]
